{"batchcomplete": "", "query": {"pages": {"1082013": {"pageid": 1082013, "ns": 0, "title": "Tynecastle Park", "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "pagelanguagehtmlcode": "en", "pagelanguagedir": "ltr", "touched": "2026-02-26T17:32:22Z", "lastrevid": 1330892336, "length": 32320, "fullurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tynecastle_Park", "editurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Tynecastle_Park&action=edit", "canonicalurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tynecastle_Park", "pageprops": {"page_image_free": "Tynecastle_before_the_Sky_Sports_Cup_Final_-_53607560077.jpg", "wikibase-shortdesc": "Football stadium in Edinburgh, Scotland", "wikibase_item": "Q1326446"}, "description": "Football stadium in Edinburgh, Scotland", "descriptionsource": "local", "extract": "Tynecastle Park, also known as Tynecastle Stadium or colloquially as Tynie, is a football stadium in the Gorgie area of Edinburgh, which is the home ground of Scottish Professional Football League club Heart of Midlothian (Hearts). A UEFA category four stadium, it has also hosted Scotland international matches, and been used as a neutral venue for Scottish Cup and Scottish League Cup semi-finals.\nTynecastle has a seating capacity of 19,852, which makes it the sixth-largest football stadium in Scotland. Hearts have played at the present site of Tynecastle since 1886.", "categories": [{"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1886 establishments in Scotland"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All Wikipedia articles written in British English"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Articles with short description"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Commons category link is on Wikidata"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Coordinates on Wikidata"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Football venues in Edinburgh"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Gorgie"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Heart of Midlothian F.C."}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Pages using gadget WikiMiniAtlas"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Rugby league stadi